circuitMIB.description: The MIB module for transport channels

circuitLoadBalanceInterval.name: circuitLoadBalanceInterval
circuitLoadBalanceInterval.description: The default load balancing schedule is to examine 1 circuit every 3 minutes at the GNE. Regardless of whether the circuit is moved to a better ring path or not, the next circuit is not examined until another 3 minutes (default) had expired. The duration of the load balance timer will be configurable from a range of 0 to 65535 seconds. Using a value of 0 will turn off load balancing.

circuitLoadBalanceNumPerInterval.name: circuitLoadBalanceNumPerInterval
circuitLoadBalanceNumPerInterval.description: Indicates the number of circuits being loadbalanced in a fixed interval. The maximum value is 10 circuits per second.

circuitOldIpAddrToSwap.name: circuitOldIpAddrToSwap
circuitOldIpAddrToSwap.description: When a chassis running several circuits has to be moved to a new location with a new different IpAddress, then all the associated circuits has to be properly modified with the new IpAddress. This object will specify the old-IpAddress. This process is almost transparent to the user, but, he will notice traffic loss due to the circuits being brought down and up.

circuitNewIpAddrToSwap.name: circuitNewIpAddrToSwap
circuitNewIpAddrToSwap.description: When a chassis running several circuits has to be moved to a new location with a new different IpAddress, then all the associated circuits has to be properly modified with the new IpAddress. This object will specify the old-IpAddress. This process is almost transparent to the user, but, he will notice traffic loss due to the circuits being brought down and up.

circuitEventInterval.name: circuitEventInterval
circuitEventInterval.description: For any circuit related events, events are generated at a specific time interval. circuitEventInterval specifies that. The default value is 1 second.

circuitEventNumPerInterval.name: circuitEventNumPerInterval
circuitEventNumPerInterval.description: This object specifies the number of events generated per interval. The default is 10 per second.

circuitTable.name: circuitTable
circuitTable.description: A table containing information about the transport channels in the system

circuitEntry.name: circuitEntry
circuitEntry.description: Entry in the table for a single transport channel

circuitSrcIpAddr.name: circuitSrcIpAddr
circuitSrcIpAddr.description: IP address of the source circuit endpoint.

circuitSrcInterfaceNum.name: circuitSrcInterfaceNum
circuitSrcInterfaceNum.description: The interface number of the source circuit endpoint.

circuitSrcConnectionID.name: circuitSrcConnectionID
circuitSrcConnectionID.description: Connection Identifier of the source circuit endpoint. Based on the protocol type, further information may be required to completely specify a circuit on a channel. For example, Ethernet VLAN requires a VLAN Id, Frame Relay requires a DLCI and ATM requires VPI and VCI. For ATM, this field is encoded as 12 bits of VPI and 16 bits of VCI.

circuitSrcDescString.name: circuitSrcDescString
circuitSrcDescString.description: Textual description of the source side of the circuit endpoint.

circuitDestIpAddr.name: circuitDestIpAddr
circuitDestIpAddr.description: IP address of the destination circuit endpoint.

circuitDestInterfaceNum.name: circuitDestInterfaceNum
circuitDestInterfaceNum.description: The interface number of the destination circuit endpoint.

circuitDestConnectionID.name: circuitDestConnectionID
circuitDestConnectionID.description: Connection Identifier of the destination circuit endpoint. Based on the protocol type, further information may be required to completely specify a circuit on a channel. For example, Ethernet VLAN requires a VLAN Id, Frame Relay requires a DLCI and ATM requires VPI and VCI. For ATM, this field is encoded as 12 bits of VPI and 16 bits of VCI.

circuitDestDescString.name: circuitDestDescString
circuitDestDescString.description: Textual description of the destination side of the circuit endpoint.

circuitName.name: circuitName
circuitName.description: CircuitName is a unique name given to a circuit.

circuitID.name: circuitID
circuitID.description: CircuitID is a unique ID given to a circuit. It is equal to the TC-ID in the PM.

circuitRowStatus.name: circuitRowStatus
circuitRowStatus.description: Indicates if a row has been created or deleted. See SNMPv2-TC for complete description.

circuitReasonText.name: circuitReasonText
circuitReasonText.description: Provides the reason for the error indicated.

circuitFailLocIpAddr.name: circuitFailLocIpAddr
circuitFailLocIpAddr.description: IP address of location where circuit failure code is encountered.

circuitFailLocSlot1.name: circuitFailLocSlot1
circuitFailLocSlot1.description: Slot number where circuit failure code is encountered.

circuitFailLocPort1.name: circuitFailLocPort1
circuitFailLocPort1.description: Port number where circuit failure code is encountered.

circuitFailLocInterfaceNum1.name: circuitFailLocInterfaceNum1
circuitFailLocInterfaceNum1.description: Interface number where circuit failure code is encountered.

circuitFailLocConnectionID1.name: circuitFailLocConnectionID1
circuitFailLocConnectionID1.description: Connection Identifier of the failed circuit endpoint.

circuitFailLocSlot2.name: circuitFailLocSlot2
circuitFailLocSlot2.description: Slot number where circuit failure code is encountered.

circuitFailLocPort2.name: circuitFailLocPort2
circuitFailLocPort2.description: Port number where circuit failure code is encountered.

circuitFailLocInterfaceNum2.name: circuitFailLocInterfaceNum2
circuitFailLocInterfaceNum2.description: Interface number where circuit failure code is encountered.

circuitFailLocConnectionID2.name: circuitFailLocConnectionID2
circuitFailLocConnectionID2.description: Connection Identifier of the failed circuit endpoint.

circuitFwdTDType.name: circuitFwdTDType
circuitFwdTDType.description: Specifies the traffic descriptor type associated with the forward traffic descriptor parameters. The forward direction is 'into the network' from the circuit endpoint. TDType is independent of the end-point protocol.

circuitFwdTDParam1.name: circuitFwdTDParam1
circuitFwdTDParam1.description: Parameter 1 of the forward traffic descriptor of type circuitFwdTdType. For type Ethernet, this value corresponds to CIR. For type Frame Relay, this value corresponds to CIR. For type ATM-CBR, this value corresponds to PCR(0+1).

circuitFwdTDParam2.name: circuitFwdTDParam2
circuitFwdTDParam2.description: Parameter 2 of the forward traffic descriptor of type circuitFwdTdType. For type Ethernet, this value corresponds to Bc. For type Frame Relay, this value corresponds to Bc.

circuitFwdTDParam3.name: circuitFwdTDParam3
circuitFwdTDParam3.description: Parameter 3 of the forward traffic descriptor of type circuitFwdTdType. For type Ethernet, this value corresponds to Be. For type Frame Relay, this value corresponds to Be.

circuitFwdTDParam4.name: circuitFwdTDParam4
circuitFwdTDParam4.description: Parameter 4 of the forward traffic descriptor of type circuitFwdTdType.

circuitBwdTDType.name: circuitBwdTDType
circuitBwdTDType.description: Specifies the traffic descriptor type associated with the backward traffic descriptor parameters. The backward direction is 'out of the network' from the circuit endpoint. TDType is independent to of the end-point protocol.

circuitBwdTDParam1.name: circuitBwdTDParam1
circuitBwdTDParam1.description: Parameter 1 of the backward traffic descriptor of type circuitBwdTdType. For type Ethernet, this value corresponds to CIR. For type Frame Relay, this value corresponds to CIR. For type ATM-CBR, this value corresponds to PCR(0+1).

circuitBwdTDParam2.name: circuitBwdTDParam2
circuitBwdTDParam2.description: Parameter 2 of the backward traffic descriptor of type circuitBwdTdType. For type Ethernet, this value corresponds to Bc. For type Frame Relay, this value corresponds to Bc.

circuitBwdTDParam3.name: circuitBwdTDParam3
circuitBwdTDParam3.description: Parameter 3 of the backward traffic descriptor of type circuitBwdTdType. For type Ethernet, this value corresponds to Be. For type Frame Relay, this value corresponds to Be.

circuitBwdTDParam4.name: circuitBwdTDParam4
circuitBwdTDParam4.description: Parameter 4 of the backward traffic descriptor of type circuitBwdTdType.

circuitClassOfService.name: circuitClassOfService
circuitClassOfService.description: Specifies the class of service for Data or non-TDM circuits. This value is in the range of 0-7 where 1 has the highest priority and 7 has the lowest.

circuitAdminState.name: circuitAdminState
circuitAdminState.description: Administrative state of the circuit. Circuits in the disabled state do not consume network resources such as bandwidth. The network continuously attempts to establish circuits until successful while in the enabled state. The 'enabledButNotUsed' state tells that the transport segment is established and network resources are assigned to it, but, traffic is not allowed to pass though it.

circuitOperState.name: circuitOperState
circuitOperState.description: Aperational state of the circuit. Circuits in the disabled state do not consume network resources such as bandwidth. The network continuously attempts to establish circuits until successful while in the enabled state.

circuitTimeSinceStatusChange.name: circuitTimeSinceStatusChange
circuitTimeSinceStatusChange.description: Gives the time (in seconds) since the most recent status change.

circuitSetupPriority.name: circuitSetupPriority
circuitSetupPriority.description: If there are insufficient network resources for establishing all transport channels, this field specifies the priority of the transport channel.

circuitHoldPriority.name: circuitHoldPriority
circuitHoldPriority.description: If a number of transport channels of a low Setup Priority need to be cleared in order to release resources allowing for a higher priority (Setup) transport channel to be established, this field specifies the Hold priority where low Hold priority transport channels are cleared before higher Hold priority transport channels.

circuitIsRedundancyReqd.name: circuitIsRedundancyReqd
circuitIsRedundancyReqd.description: Specifies if the circuit is to be established over rings that are logically configured as 'protected'. A protected ring could physically be in a fault state where one fiber has failed. A circuit that requires redundancy will be established over rings logically configured as 'protected' even though the current physical state of a protected ring may be in a fault state.

circuitPreferredEP1OptSlot.name: circuitPreferredEP1OptSlot
circuitPreferredEP1OptSlot.description: If the circuit spans one or two rings, this is the slot number of the first preferred ring. Preferred rings allow a manual overide of the routed circuit path.

circuitPreferredEP1OptPort.name: circuitPreferredEP1OptPort
circuitPreferredEP1OptPort.description: If the circuit spans one or two rings, this is the port number of the first preferred ring.

circuitPreferredEP1OptVport.name: circuitPreferredEP1OptVport
circuitPreferredEP1OptVport.description: If the circuit spans one or two rings, this is the lambda number of the first preferred ring.

circuitPreferredEP2OptSlot.name: circuitPreferredEP2OptSlot
circuitPreferredEP2OptSlot.description: If the circuit spans two rings, this is the slot number of the second preferred ring. Preferred rings allow a manual overide of the routed circuit path.

circuitPreferredEP2OptPort.name: circuitPreferredEP2OptPort
circuitPreferredEP2OptPort.description: If the circuit spans two rings, this is the port number of the second preferred ring.

circuitPreferredEP2OptVport.name: circuitPreferredEP2OptVport
circuitPreferredEP2OptVport.description: If the circuit spans two rings, this is the lambda number of the second preferred ring.

circuitUseAlternateRing.name: circuitUseAlternateRing
circuitUseAlternateRing.description: Allows operator to specify whether an alternate ring can be used if the preferred ring(s) fail. This requires the ability to load-balance back onto the preferred ring once it becomes available. The format for this field is Boolean.

circuitInFrames.name: circuitInFrames
circuitInFrames.description: Number of frames received at the ingress point and passed on to the circuit.

circuitInDEFrames.name: circuitInDEFrames
circuitInDEFrames.description: Number of frames received at the ingress point and passed on to the circuit.

circuitInOctets.name: circuitInOctets
circuitInOctets.description: Number of octets received at the ingress point and passed on to the circuit.

circuitInDEOctets.name: circuitInDEOctets
circuitInDEOctets.description: Number of octets received at the ingress point and passed on to the circuit.

circuitInCLP0Cells.name: circuitInCLP0Cells
circuitInCLP0Cells.description: Number of cells received at the ingress point and passed on to the circuit.

circuitInCLP1Cells.name: circuitInCLP1Cells
circuitInCLP1Cells.description: Number of cells received at the ingress point and passed on to the circuit.

circuitInFramesDiscard.name: circuitInFramesDiscard
circuitInFramesDiscard.description: Number of frames received at the ingress point but are discarded due to the non-conformance of the contract, i.e., it exceeds the traffic contract (BE).

circuitInDEFramesDiscard.name: circuitInDEFramesDiscard
circuitInDEFramesDiscard.description: Number of frames received at the ingress point but are discarded due to the non-conformance of the contract, i.e., it exceeds the traffic contract (BE).

circuitInOctetsDiscard.name: circuitInOctetsDiscard
circuitInOctetsDiscard.description: Number of octets received at the ingress point but are discarded due to the non-conformance of the contract, i.e., it exceeds the traffic contract (BE).

circuitInDEOctetsDiscard.name: circuitInDEOctetsDiscard
circuitInDEOctetsDiscard.description: Number of octets received at the ingress point but are discarded due to the non-conformance of the contract, i.e., it exceeds the traffic contract (BE).

circuitInCLP0CellsDiscard.name: circuitInCLP0CellsDiscard
circuitInCLP0CellsDiscard.description: Number of octets received at the ingress point but are discarded due to the non-conformance of the contract, i.e., it exceeds the traffic contract (BE).

circuitInCLP1CellsDiscard.name: circuitInCLP1CellsDiscard
circuitInCLP1CellsDiscard.description: Number of octets received at the ingress point but are discarded due to the non-conformance of the contract, i.e., it exceeds the traffic contract (BE).

circuitInFramesTagged.name: circuitInFramesTagged
circuitInFramesTagged.description: Number of tagged frames received. A tagged frame represents non-conforming frames to the contract (when CIR < frame contract < BE). In these frames, the DE (Discard Enable) is set.

circuitInOctetsTagged.name: circuitInOctetsTagged
circuitInOctetsTagged.description: Number of tagged octets received. A tagged octet represents non-conforming octet to the contract (when CIR < octet contract < BE).In these octets, the DE (Discard Enable) is set.

circuitInCLP0CellsTagged.name: circuitInCLP0CellsTagged
circuitInCLP0CellsTagged.description: Number of tagged octets received. A tagged octet represents non-conforming octet to the contract (when CIR < octet contract < BE).In these octets, the DE (Discard Enable) is set.

circuitOutFrames.name: circuitOutFrames
circuitOutFrames.description: Number of frames sent out through the circuit.

circuitOutDEFrames.name: circuitOutDEFrames
circuitOutDEFrames.description: Number of frames sent out through the circuit.

circuitOutOctets.name: circuitOutOctets
circuitOutOctets.description: Number of octets sent out through the circuit.

circuitOutDEOctets.name: circuitOutDEOctets
circuitOutDEOctets.description: Number of octets sent out through the circuit.

circuitOutCLP0Cells.name: circuitOutCLP0Cells
circuitOutCLP0Cells.description: Number of cells sent out through the circuit.

circuitOutCLP1Cells.name: circuitOutCLP1Cells
circuitOutCLP1Cells.description: Number of cells sent out through the circuit.

circuitInactive.name: circuitInactive
circuitInactive.description: Indicates that the circuit became inactive and specifies the reason for it becoming inactive

circuitActive.name: circuitActive
circuitActive.description: Indicates that the circuit became active

circuitLoadBalancing.name: circuitLoadBalancing
circuitLoadBalancing.description: Indicates that the circuit underwent load balancing
